alikiwhitfield
Tamborine Mountain, Australia24 contributions
1
ENVIRONMENTAL DISASTER
Oct 2016
Halong Bay was something I built a lot of excitement over. However, the postcard perfect pictures should be retaken with the smog, vessel fumes & thin layer of oily pollution on the water.

It was so sad to see. The ocean has no sparkle left. There was 'western' rubbish floating in the water & it was packed to the gunnels with junk boats & shuttles all spewing grey diesel fumes.
The solitary fishing village is struggling to survive & there is very little bird life.
Swimming in the bay, we could taste the pollution on our lips & feel it on our skin.
For thousands of years Halong Bay was home to 3500 fishing families who were asked to leave & displaced in order to make way for tourism. Uneducated, many of them could not find jobs in the city. It ruined an ancient way of life... And ruined this natural wonder.
The limestone outcrops were still beautiful. But I left feeling sad. It's. 'world heritage listing' is an absolute farce.... as it won't be 'inherited' by anyone. It's ecosystem & majesty will be dead for future generations without dramatic/harsh change that sacrifices much of the tourists $
Written October 22, 2016
Rouge_fairy
Makati, Philippines578 contributions
