Roxanne L
Melbourne, Australia17 contributions
Beautiful but dirty. Don't swim!
Sep 2016 ‚Ä¢ Family
Just visited the bay on the Dragon Pearly (which was really good). Felt compelled to write about our experience. The bay and port look terrible. You instantly question the sustainability of the bay with so many tourists AND tankers around. I have also, while travelling inVietnam, been reading "Vietnam, Rising Dragon" by Bill Haystock. This prompted me to think about the health of the Bay, as the government is highly unlikely to make the environment a high priority over growth and employment. After more research I discovered in 2015 there were devastating floods in the area which caused the "local" coal mine to flood and the toxic wastes were sent flowing into the bay. There are lots of comments about sewage issues but I think his is the least of the concerns. The coal mine toxins are shocking poisons. My daughter swam in the Bay as the tour company didn't say there were any issues with water safety. It has only occurred to me now that my daughter smelled really bad later that evening. I now realise it was the water. Do not swim in the Bay. It still looks beautiful and once your away from the crowds it is very peaceful. But the government needs to implement some strategies urgently before it is lost forever.
Written September 30, 2016
